FILE
	/usr/common/sys/exitd.c

NAME
	get_exit_segments - get all segments containing exits

PROTOTYPE
	int *get_exit_segments(void)

CALLED BY
	System, Common, Game

DESCRIPTION
	Returns an array of integer indices for all segments containing
	exit objects.  Exits are kept in different segments than other
	Phantasmal objects like rooms, portables or mobiles.

RETURN VALUE
	An array of integers, or nil.

ERRORS
	Usually none.

SEE ALSO
	get_exit_by_num, get_all_exits, exits_in_segment
